-- File: supabase/migrations/00120_re_import_eleven_point.sql
-- Eleven Point was imported in 00116 with the AR portion of the river
-- only (lat 36.15–36.585), because dissolveLongest in
-- scripts/import-nhd-rivers-from-tnm.ts picked the longest connected
-- NHDFlowline component and the river is split across 9 components in
-- HUC8 11010011 due to ~400 m digitization gaps. The MO main stem
-- (lat 36.59–36.82) was dropped, and every Eleven Point access point
-- got snapped onto the AR portion via the auto_snap_access_point
-- trigger.
--
-- The import script now soft-bridges component endpoints within
-- ~1.2 km, recovering the full chain (94.1 mi instead of 49.3 mi).
-- This migration replaces just the eleven-point row with the corrected
-- LineString. After applying, re-run scripts/snap-access-points.ts to
-- pull the access points off the truncated AR portion onto the real
-- river.

